Hello.  If you are reading this, you're probably really, really bored.  Because I'm really bored typing it.  But thank you for reading it.   I'm gonna tell you about my shedule for the week.  I wake up at 9 in the morning because I hear the phone ring from the idiotic salepeople, tell them not to wake me up or I will hire a hit man to kill them in a gruesome way, then go on the internet.  I then eat breakfast as I read other people's lj's and dj's.  Then, I water the lawn, clean my room, and start the laundry.   By now, it's 11, so I start updating my own lj, and chat with whoever's on.   At 12, I go eat lunch and watch whatever's on MTV, or VH1 for an hour.  At 1, I stop what I'm doing and watch Days Of Our Lives, and then Passions(don't ask why) At three, I go back on the Internet and do whatever.  Then I wait till my mom comes home, and then go to softball gmes or practices.  THen I come home and watch T.V. or go on the internet till I go to bed at 11:30.  Interesting, huh?

It's surprising that, while I have nothing to do during my break, I don't feel the urge to update my journal.  And I ask myself, why?  Why do I feel I need to plan my shedule around soap operas?  Why does my mom assume I have friends?  Why do Roshni and Jordan find pleasure in hellish dolls?  And most importantly, why is Disney trying to corrupt the minds of the little children by encouraging them to sing the timeless question, "high hoe?"(if you don't know. don't ask).  I don't know, guess I have a bit to ponder.  Also, I've decided not to divorce any of my spouses because they yelled at me.  Now, I'm sooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo bored that I'm gonna end by saying that we waste words on lowercase and capitals.
